    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i guess it's a bit of a toss-up then. but when you look at the actual math of how fast we need to cut carbon, does it feel like we even have a choice? like, can we realistically hit net zero with just solar and wind, or is nuclear just kind of a necessary evil at this point?",
