      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The math of climate science is stark: we cannot realistically hit net zero using only solar and wind because their intermittency and current storage limitations make them insufficient for baseload power. Nuclear energy is not merely a \"necessary evil\" but a critical, proven technology that scales reliably to bridge the gap between current infrastructure and deep decarbonization targets. Without it, the path to limiting global warming to 1.5°C becomes mathematically impossible, regardless of how much we invest in renewables.",
      "source": "target",
