    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, so you're saying it's basically a fact that it's impossible without nuclear? that seems like a pretty huge claim to make when so many scientists and policy experts are still arguing that better battery tech or different grid management could make renewables work. aren't you just ignoring the side that thinks nuclear is too risky or too slow to build?",
